# DSA Lesson Structure Conventions

## Folder naming

- Phase folders: `phase-{n}/` (e.g. `phase-0`, `phase-1`)
- Lesson folders: `phase-{n}/lesson-{spelled-number}/` (e.g. `lesson-ten`, not `lesson-10`)
- Lesson markdown: `{topic-slug}.md` in kebab-case (e.g. `stacks-lifo.md`)
- Lesson python file: `{topic-slug}.py` matching the markdown slug (e.g. `stacks-lifo.py`)
- LeetCode challenge: `leetcode-challenge.py` in each lesson folder (no coded solution, leave as `pass`)

## Markdown structure

- Title: `# Phase {N} – Lesson {X}: {Title}`
- Blockquote hook after title
- Numbered sections: `## 1. Title`, `## 2. Title`
- Fenced Python code blocks (no HTML in markdown files)
- End with a "Key Takeaway" section

## Phase index.html structure

- Drawer nav: every phase lists all phases with lesson links
- Lessons use `<article id="lesson-{X}" data-lesson-section class="lesson">` (alternate `lesson-alt`)
- Lesson headers: `lesson-number` (zero-padded, e.g. `08`), `lesson-title`, `lesson-subtitle`
- Content sections: `<div class="content-block fade-in">`
- Each lesson ends with `where-we-are` and `what-next` sections
- Code uses span classes: `keyword`, `function`, `number`, `string`, `comment`

## Lesson python file

- Contains key code examples from the lesson with inline comments
- Working code, not a challenge — all implementations complete
- Reference: `phase-2/lesson-eight/linked-list.py`, `phase-0/lesson-four/linear-search.py`

## LeetCode challenge file

- Docstring with: Problem title, statement, function signature, example, key insight, expected complexity
- Helper classes (e.g. Node) if needed
- Function body left as `pass` — do not write the coded solution
- Test calls at the bottom
